  <p>Trees Puzzle is a content site about tree games, printable activities, and outdoor learning ideas. The goal is simple: make it easier for adults to turn everyday nature observations into structured play.</p>
  <p>The site is written for parents, teachers, homeschool families, camp leaders, and anyone building low-prep activities around trees, leaves, bark, cones, seeds, and seasonal change.</p>
  <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-white pt-4">Editorial approach</h2>
  <p>We prioritize activities that are easy to explain, flexible across age groups, and realistic to run with common supplies. We avoid thin listicles and instead build pages around usable instructions, clue formats, and examples.</p>
  <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-white pt-4">Trust and safety</h2>
  <p>All content is designed to be family-friendly. Safety notes are included where outdoor movement or collecting natural materials is involved, and the site separates educational content from any future advertising or sponsorships.</p>
</ContentPageLayout>
